The paper deals with training large recurrent language models with user-level differential privacy guarantees, which involves techniques from machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of federated learning (cs.DS) and stochastic gradient descent (cs.AI) in achieving differential privacy. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely to be relevant to this paper.
